 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2454/how-to-configure-right-click-menu-colours/?answer=2456#post-id-2456</link><description>I agree with sur5r. The context menus for applications will be configured based on the gui toolkit used to build them. If they are kde apps, the settings will be in ~/.kde or ~/.kde4. The following link describes how to set on a per-app basis: http://forum.kde.org/viewtopic.php?f=17&amp;t=90720.</description><pubDate>Thu, 29 Aug 2013 10:10:53 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2454/how-to-configure-right-click-menu-colours/?answer=2456#post-id-2456</guid></item><item><title>Answer by sur5r for &lt;p&gt;Currently the right click menu, and any drop down menus are a windows-98 esque blue on grey. Is there any way of changing this? (GTK apps show up using the default gtk theme, however I don't use many GTK apps). I have read a guide on how to change the colors, but it only described changing the window titles.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2454/how-to-configure-right-click-menu-colours/?answer=2455#post-id-2455</link><description> I highly doubt this is really an i3 related question. Colors like those in context menus depend on the particular application you are running or the graphics toolkit it is using.</description><pubDate>Thu, 29 Aug 2013 06:53:04 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2454/how-to-configure-right-click-menu-colours/?answer=2455#post-id-2455</guid></item></channel></rss>